![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/72d7c341-b9f9-4b24-81e1-feea54b2de43/384.jpg)

This week on the _Major Issues Podcast_, we're diving headfirst into _SIEGE_ – Marvel’s all-out, no-holds-barred event where Norman Osborn loses his damn mind and decides it’s a good idea to attack Asgard. Yeah, _that_ Asgard. With the Avengers scattered, the Sentry going full horror movie, and every hero caught in the crossfire, this four-issue war changes everything. We’re talking betrayal, redemption, brutal takedowns, and the fall of a madman’s empire. How did we get here? Who doesn’t make it out alive? And why does this event still hit so hard? Get ready – the road to Heroic Age starts here!

Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

